<topcClas>Trade, industry and markets - Industry and management</topcClas>       </subject>       <abstract><p>Abstract copyright UK Data Service and data collection copyright owner.</p>The <i>OECD International Trade by Commodities Statistics</i> (ITCS) database (Standard International Trade Classification (SITC) Revision 2) contains annual time-series data from 1961 onwards on foreign trade of the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development's (OECD) member countries and selected non-OECD countries (China, Hong Kong China and Chinese Taipei). It provides detailed data on commodity and partner country in value and in quantity. The 2005 version of the database contains data up to 2004.<br> <br> These data were first provided by the UK Data Service in February 2006. The UK Data Service  web site includes further information on their OECD International Trade by Commodities Statistics holdings, including a <a href="http://www.esds.ac.uk/International/support/dataset_guides.asp" title="OECD International Trade by Commodities Statistics dataset user guide">dataset user guide</a> and details of <a href="http://www.esds.ac.uk/international/news/dataupdate.asp#oecditcsnd" title="OECD International Trade by Commodities Statistics latest database updates">latest database updates<a/>.<br> <br> <b>Citation:</b> The bibliographic citation for the database is: Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (<i>{YYYY}</i>): International Trade By Commodities Statistics (<i>{Ed. Data download: YYYY-MM}</i>). Mimas, University of Manchester. DOI: <i>{edition specific doi - e.g. <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.5257/oecd/itcs/2007">http://dx.doi.org/10.5257/oecd/itcs/2007</a>}</i>. <br> <br> <b>Alternative DOIs:</b> <a href="http://www.oecd-ilibrary.org/science-and-technology/data/oecd-science-technology-and-r-d-statistics_strd-data-en" title="10.1787/itcs-data-en">10.1787/itcs-data-en</a> (to access via OECD.Stat subscription).<br> </abstract>       <abstract><B>Main Topics</B>:<br>The database covers:<ul><li>trade</li><li>commodities</li><li>products</li><li>goods</li></ul></abstract>       <sumDscr>         <collDate>The OECD ITCS database runs from 1961 onwards.</collDate>         <nation>Multi-nation</nation>         <geogUnit>Countries</geogUnit>         <anlyUnit>Administrative units (geographical/political)</anlyUnit>         <universe>Cross-national; National</universe>         <universe>Countries covered include the 30 OECD Member reporting countries: Australia, Austria, Belgium, Canada, Czech Republic, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Ireland, Italy, Japan, Korea, Luxembourg, Mexico, Netherlands, New Zealand, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Slovak Republic, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Turkey, United Kingdom, United States, and three non-OECD countries: China, Hong Kong China and Chinese Taipei. The database also covers 260 partner countries - see the 'OECD ITCS Definitions and Country notes' link in the <a href=" http://www.esds.ac.uk/international/support/dataset_guides.asp" title=" OECD dataset user guide"> dataset user guide</a>  for details.</universe>         <dataKind>Numeric data</dataKind>         <dataKind> Aggregate (macro) level</dataKind>       </sumDscr>     </stdyInfo>     <method>       <dataColl>         <timeMeth>Time Series</timeMeth>         <timeMeth>the database is updated annually</timeMeth>         <sampProc>See user guide for details.</sampProc>         <collMode>See user guide for details.</collMode>         <sources />         <weight>See user guide for details.</weight>       </dataColl>     </method>     <dataAccs>       <setAvail>         <accsPlac>UK Data Service</accsPlac>       </setAvail>       <useStmt>         <specPerm>Restricted access</specPerm>         <restrctn>Registration is required and standard conditions of use apply.
